20in%20size.%20He%20is%20from%20Sweden%20and%20he%20was%20there%20to%20play%20soccer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20graduated%20in%20May%202020%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I%20was%20offered%20a%20temporary%20teaching%20job%20in%20Madrid%2C%20Spain.%20I%20went%20there%20to%20teach%20English%2C%20and%20my%20boyfriend%20followed%20me%20there.%20While%20we%20both%20knew%20our%20stay%20in%20Madrid%20would%20be%20temporary%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20be%20together%20long-term.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20do%20that%2C%20we%20had%20two%20options%3A%20we%20could%20either%20move%20back%20to%20the%20US%2C%20or%20I%20could%20follow%20him%20to%20Sweden.%20We%20chose%20Sweden%20because%20it%20was%20easier%20for%20me%20to%20get%20a%20visa%20there%20than%20it%20was%20for%20him%20to%20get%20one%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20moving%20to%20Sweden%2C%20I've%20noticed%20some%20differences%20that%20have%20surprised%20me.%20Some%20are%20small%2C%20but%20others%20have%20really%20stood%20out%20to%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Swedes%20can%20be%20really%20quiet%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20moved%20to%20Stockholm%2C%20the%20capital%20of%20Sweden%2C%20I%20was%20shocked%20by%20how%20quiet%20people%20are.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20I%20take%20the%20metro%2C%20our%20metro%20car%20will%20be%20silent%20%E2%80%94%20even%20during%20rush%20hour.%20Instead%20of%20talking%20like%20they%20would%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Swedes%20will%20usually%20sit%20quietly%20and%20try%20not%20to%20bother%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20grocery%20store%20is%20another%20good%20example%20of%20this.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20you%20might%20strike%20up%20a%20conversation%20with%20the%20cashier%20%E2%80%94%20but%20here%20in%20Sweden%20that%20isn't%20common.%20Instead%2C%20the%20people%20often%20keep%20to%20themselves%20and%20don't%20participate%20in%20%26quot%3Bsmall%20talk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Swedes%20leave%20their%20strollers%20and%20babies%20outside%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20when%20I%20walk%20past%20a%20cafe%2C%20I%20will%20see%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fnordic-parents-nap-babies-subzero-temperatures-sleep-better-2020-1%5C%22%3Eunattended%20stroller%20parked%20outside%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20baby%20napping%20in%20it.%20Before%20moving%20here%2C%20I%20always%20saw%20Sweden%20as%20a%20safe%20country%2C%20where%20people%20trust%20each%20other.%20But%20when%20I%20saw%20this%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20it%20made%20me%20feel%20even%20safer.%20I%20don't%20think%C2%A0I've%20ever%20seen%20this%20happen%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20it%20says%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20trust%20Swedes%20have%20in%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20believe%20the%20fresh%20air%20is%20good%20for%20babies'%20immune%20systems%20and%20that%20it%20toughens%20them%20up%20for%20the%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20There's%20more%20work-life%20balance%20in%20Sweden%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20in%20Sweden%2C%20they%20want%20you%20to%20take%20your%20vacation%20days.%20After%20you%20work%20for%20a%20company%20for%20a%20full%20year%2C%20you%20are%20entitled%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsweden-work-life-balance-american-expat-happiness-burnout-2023-5%5C%22%3E25%20working%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20paid%20vacation%2C%20or%20five%20work%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20months%2C%20you're%20allowed%20to%20take%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsweden-us-work-life-balance-differences-2019-8%5C%22%3Efour%20of%20those%20weeks%20%3C%2Fa%3Eoff%20consecutively.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20home%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20have%20friends%20who%20are%20only%20allowed%20to%20take%2010%20days%20off%20a%20year.%20So%20I%20was%20pleasantly%20surprised%20by%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20you%20can%20take%20off%20here%20in%20Sweden.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20maternity%20and%20paternity%20leave%2C%20new%20parents%20in%20Sweden%20are%20able%20to%20take%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsweden.se%2Flife%2Fsociety%2Fwork-life-balance%23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E480%20days%20off%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecombined%20for%20each%20child%20they%20have.%20This%20time%20off%20is%20also%20paid%20and%20allows%20for%20both%20parents%20to%20stay%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20It%20gets%20dark%20early%20in%20December%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20big%20thing%20that%20really%20surprised%20me%20in%20Sweden%20was%20how%20dark%20it%20gets%20in%20December.%20During%20December%2C%20we%20get%20very%20little%20daylight%20each%20day.%20In%20Stockholm%20for%20example%2C%20we%20get%20roughly%20five%20to%20six%20hours%20of%20daylight%2C%20and%20the%20sun%20sets%20around%203%20p.m.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20during%20the%20%26quot%3Bbrightest%26quot%3B%20part%20of%20the%20day%2C%20it's%20usually%20so%20cloudy%20and%20gloomy%2C%20you%20can't%20see%20the%20sun%20either%20way.%20I%20remember%20experiencing%20it%20for%20the%20first%20time%20and%20wondering%20if%20I%20could%20go%20through%20it%20again.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20did%2C%20and%20I%20made%20it%20through%20a%20second%20time.%20This%20year%2C%20however%2C%20I'm%20hoping%20to%20escape%20it%20and%20am%20currently%20looking%20for%20flights%20to%20somewhere%20more%20warm%20and%20sunny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Swedes%20remove%20their%20shoes%20at%20the%20doctor's%20office%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20you%20might%20take%20your%20shoes%20off%20when%20going%20into%20people's%20homes%2C%20but%20here%20in%20Sweden%2C%20there%20are%20other%20places%20where%20you%20must%20remove%20your%20shoes.%20The%20doctor's%20office%20is%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20heading%20to%20the%20doctor%2C%20and%20when%20I%20realized%20I%20needed%20to%20remove%20my%20shoes%2C%20I%20felt%20weird%20about%20it.%20I%20had%20never%20done%20that%20before%20and%20it%20felt%20funny%20standing%20in%20my%20socks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20see%20why%20they%20do%20it%2C%20it's%20for%20hygiene.%20And%20if%20you%20have%20to%20remove%20your%20shoes%2C%20they%20will%20have%20a%20rack%20for%20you%20to%20put%20your%20shoes%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESince%20leaving%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20things%20that%20have%20surprised%20me%2C%20like%20the%20alcohol%20is%20more%20expensive%20in%20Sweden%2C%20and%20you%20can't%20buy%20alcohol%20on%20Sundays.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESwedes%20are%20also%20really%20into%20their%20candy%20here.%20Every%20Saturday%20they%20have%20what's%20called%20%26quot%3BL%C3%B6rdagsgodis%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20means%20%26quot%3BSaturday%20sweets.%26quot%3B%20Everyone%20goes%20out%20and%20buys%20a%20bag%20of%20candy%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20cute%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20things%20I%20miss%20about%20the%20US%2C%20of%20course.%20I%20miss%20my%20family%2C%20my%20friends%20and%20I%20miss%20the%20beach%20I%20used%20to%20go%20to.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20mainly%2C%20I%20miss%20the%20small%20conversations%20and%20the%20small%20talk%2C%20the%20kind%20you%20have%20when%20you're%20at%20a%20grocery%20store%2C%20or%20when%20you're%20out%20running%20an%20errand.%20While%20it's%20not%20a%20bad%20thing%20that%20Swedes%20don't%20make%20small%20talk%20as%20much%2C%20I%20do%20miss%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20left%20the%20US%20for%20another%20country%20and%20want%20to%20share%20your%20story%2C%20email%20Alyshia%20Hull%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aahull%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eahull%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-sweden-from-the-us-culture-shock-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694683981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650063c44717fd0019fca178%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsi