o-frame-police-briefing-guidelines-237700%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20should%20be%20ensured%20that%20the%20disclosure%20%5Bof%20information%5D%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20result%20in%20a%20media%20trial%20so%20as%20to%20allow%20pre-determination%20of%20the%20guilt%20of%20the%20accused.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20apex%20court%20also%20directed%20Director%20Generals%20of%20Police%20(DGPs)%20of%20all%20states%20to%20submit%20their%20suggestions%20for%20the%20manual%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20input%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20(NHRC)%20would%20be%20considered%20in%20this%20matter%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fpolice-briefing-should-not-result-in-media-trial-supreme-court-directs-mha-to-frame-police-briefing-guidelines-237700%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%20emphasised%20the%20growing%20significance%20of%20this%20issue%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMedia%20trials%20are%20liable%20to%20result%20in%20a%20deflection%20of%20the%20course%20of%20justice%20by%20impacting%20upon%20the%20evidence%20which%20would%20be%20adduced%20and%20its%20assessment%20by%20the%20adjudicating%20authorities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20noted%20that%20the%20matter%20involved%20several%20layers%20of%20public%20interest%2C%20including%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20know%20during%20an%20investigation%2C%20the%20potential%20impact%20of%20police%20disclosure%20on%20the%20investigation%20process%2C%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20and%20the%20overall%20administration%20of%20justice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fbackstory-all-media-trials-have-a-secret-ingredient%5C%22%3EBackstory%3A%20All%20Media%20Trials%20Have%20a%20Secret%20Ingredient%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20bench%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fpolice-briefing-should-not-result-in-media-trial-supreme-court-directs-mha-to-frame-police-briefing-guidelines-237700%5C%22%3Eobserved%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20existing%20guidelines%20on%20the%20subject%20were%20prepared%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20%E2%80%9Cover%20a%20decade%20ago%20on%20April%201%2C%202010%E2%80%9D%20and%20added%20that%20%E2%80%9Csince%20then%2C%20with%20the%20upsurge%20in%20reporting%20on%20crimes%20not%20only%20in%20the%20print%20media%20but%20in%20the%20electronic%20and%20social%20media%2C%20it%20becomes%20extremely%20important%20that%20there%20should%20be%20there%20should%20be%20a%20standard%20operating%20procedure%20which%20balances%20out%20all%20the%20considerations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20had%20earlier%20appointed%20senior%20advocate%20Gopal%20Sankaranarayanan%20as%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eamicus%20curiae%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20assistance.%20Sankaranarayanan%20recommended%20that%20while%20the%20media%20cannot%20be%20restrained%20from%20reporting%2C%20the%20sources%20of%20information%2C%20which%20are%20often%20government%20entities%2C%20can%20be%20regulated.%20This%20approach%20aims%20to%20prevent%20multiple%20versions%20of%20events%20from%20being%20presented%20to%20the%20media%2C%20as%20has%20happened%20in%20previous%20cases%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20restrain%20the%20media%20from%20reporting.%20But%20the%20sources%20can%20be%20restrained.%20Because%20the%20source%20is%20the%20state.%20Even%20in%20the%20Aarushi%20case%2C%20so%20many%20versions%20were%20given%20to%20the%20media%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fpolice-briefing-should-not-result-in-media-trial-supreme-court-directs-mha-to-frame-police-briefing-guidelines-237700%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20senior%20advocate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fpolice-briefing-should-not-result-in-media-trial-supreme-court-directs-mha-to-frame-police-briefing-guidelines-237700%5C%22%3Ealso%20submitted%20guidelines%20to%20be%20considered%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20framing%20the%20manual.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20guidelines%20are%20based%20on%20the%20Media%20Relations%20Handbook%20of%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20Police%20Department(LAPD)%20and%20the%20New%20York%20Police%20Department(NYPD)%2C%20along%20with%20the%20Communications%20Advisory%20of%20the%20Association%20of%20Chief%20Police%20Officers%20of%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20even%20the%20CBI%20manual.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fpress-freedom-trial-by-media-supreme-court%5C%22%3EWhere%20Does%20Press%20Freedom%20End%20and%20Trial%20by%20Media%20Begin%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20emphasised%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fpolice-briefing-should-not-result-in-media-trial-supreme-court-directs-mha-to-frame-police-briefing-guidelines-237700%5C%22%3Edelicate%20balance%20between%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20free%20speech%20and%20expression%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20accused%20to%20a%20fair%20investigation%2C%20and%20the%20privacy%20of%20victims.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CMedia%20reportage%20which%20implicates%20an%20accused%20is%20unfair.%20Biassed%20reporting%20also%20gives%20rise%20to%20public%20suspicion%20that%20the%20person%20has%20committed%20an%20offence.%20The%20media%20reports%20can%20also%20violate%20the%20privacy%20of%20victims%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20observed%20in%20the%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20also%20recognised%20that%20the%20nature%20of%20information%20disclosed%20to%20the%20media%20should%20be%20tailored%20to%20the%20specific%20circumstances%20of%20each%20case%2C%20taking%20into%20account%20factors%20such%20as%20the%20age%20and%20gender%20of%20victims%20and%20accused%20individuals.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20case%20is%20scheduled%20for%20the%20next%20hearing%20in%20the%20second%20week%20of%20January%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694677814000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-directs-mha-to-frame-rules-for-cop-press-briefings-says-disclosure-cant-result-in-media-trial%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'It%20should%20be%20ensured%20that%20the%20disclosure%20%5Bof%20information%5D%20doesn't%20result%20in%20a%20media%20trial%20so%20as%20to%20allow%20pre-determination%20of%20the%20guilt%20of%20the%20accused%2C'%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-directs-mha-to-frame-rules-for-cop-press-briefings-says-disclosure-cant-result-in-media-trial%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meta%20Quest%202%20games%20%26amp%3B%20apps%2C%20plus%20how%20to%20play%20Steam%20games%20on%20the%20VR%20headset%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EYou%20can%20play%20Steam%20games%20on%20the%20Quest%202%20by%20linking%20your%20virtual%20reality%20headset%20to%20a%20computer.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYou%20can%20access%20Steam%20VR%20games%20with%20a%20USB%20link%20cable%20or%20a%20wireless%20Air%20Link%20connection.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYour%20PC%20needs%20to%20meet%20the%20Quest%202's%20minimum%20system%20requirements%2C%20and%20you'll%20need%20to%20install%20the%20Oculus%20desktop%20app%20(along%20with%20the%20Steam%20desktop%20app).%3C%2Fli%