mha)%2C%20unchanged%20from%20last%20month%20and%20down%201%25%20from%20last%20year.%20Yield%20(on%20a%20rough%20basis)%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%204.21%20tonnes%20per%20hectare%2C%20down%201%25%C2%A0from%20last%20month%20and%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202023%20southwest%20monsoon%20is%20poised%20to%20be%20the%20lowest%20in%20eight%20years.%20The%20report%20notes%20that%20for%20India%2C%20the%20rainfall%20deficit%20was%20at%20least%208%25%20below%20the%20long-term%20average%2C%20as%20of%20September%201.%20Rainfall%20has%20been%20uneven%20for%20much%20of%20this%20monsoon%2C%20with%20August%20being%20one%20of%20the%20driest%20months%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20two%20areas%20of%20concern%20include%20the%20Indo%20Gangetic%20Plain%20in%20the%20east%2C%20which%20consist%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20and%20Odisha%2C%20and%20the%20northwest%20states%20of%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Indo%20Gangetic%20Plain%2C%20which%20comprises%20about%2030%25%20of%20total%20kharif%20rice%2C%20experienced%20below-normal%20rainfall%20as%20the%20crop%20entered%20the%20vegetative%20stage%20in%20August.%20However%2C%20in%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%2C%20farmers%20experienced%20too%20much%20rainfall%20and%20had%20to%20replant%20in%20late%20July%2C%20the%20USDA%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694672136000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F03164309%2FDSC2224-1024x684-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fusda-india-rabi-kharif-rice-less-august-monsoon%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20yield%20for%202022-2023%20was%20136%20million%20metric%20tonnes%2C%20USDA's%20projected%20yield%20for%202023-2024%20September%20is%20132%20million%20metric%20tonnes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fusda-india-rabi-k