.%20Most%20of%20the%20work%20is%20automated.%20For%20example%2C%20from%20collecting%20eggs%20from%20broilers%20and%20giving%20feed%20to%20poultry%20birds%2C%20to%20collecting%20their%20excreta%2C%20everything%20is%20ensured%20using%20machines%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20in%202013%2C%20he%20was%20selected%20by%20the%20state%20government%20as%20one%20of%20the%2080%20progressive%20farmers%20to%20be%20sent%20to%20Europe%20for%20a%2010-day%20trip%20to%20understand%20the%20nitty-gritty%20of%20expanding%20the%20farming%20business%20with%20machinery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Famravati-1694610755.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%202022%2C%20Ravindra%20was%20also%20conferred%20with%20the%20prestigious%20Jagjivan%20Ram%20Abhinav%20Kisan%20Puraskar%20by%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Agricultural%20Research%20(ICAR).%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Famravati-1694610755.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Famravati-1694610755-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Famravati-1694610755-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Famravati-1694610755-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Famravati-1694610755-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-329819%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EIn%202022%2C%20Ravindra%20was%20also%20conferred%20with%20the%20prestigious%20Jagjivan%20Ram%20Abhinav%20Kisan%20Puraskar%20by%20the%20ICAR.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20year%2C%20he%20was%20conferred%20with%20the%20Vasantrao%20Naik%20Award%20by%20the%20Maharashtra%20Government.%20Later%20in%202021%2C%20he%20received%20the%20Innovative%20Farmer%20Award%20from%20the%20Indian%20Agricultural%20Research%20Institute%20(IARI).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Ravindra%20was%20also%20conferred%20with%20the%20prestigious%20Jagjivan%20Ram%20Abhinav%20Kisan%20Puraskar%20by%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Agricultural%20Research%20(ICAR).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20because%20of%20these%20awards%20that%20Ravindra%20says%20that%20he%20was%20able%20to%20establish%20an%20identity%20and%20free%20himself%20from%20corrupt%20officers%20at%20the%20grassroots.%20%E2%80%9CMany%20local%20officers%20used%20to%20come%20to%20me%20to%20get%20hens%20and%20eggs%20for%20free%20on%20a%20regular%20basis.%20If%20denied%2C%20they%20would%20provoke%20neighbours%20to%20complain%20against%20me%20for%20bad%20odour%20coming%20from%20my%20poultry%20farm%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20this%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CUsually%2C%20the%20Government%20announces%20compensation%20when%20farmers%20experience%20crop%20losses.%20For%20this%2C%20%3Cem%3Epatwari%20%3C%2Fem%3E(village%20registrar)%20is%20appointed%20to%20survey%20the%20damage.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20they%20seek%20a%20share%20in%20the%20compensation%20amount.%20If%20somebody%20refuses%20to%20give%20the%20amount%2C%20they%20remove%20their%20names%20from%20the%20list.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERavindra%20says%20he%20was%20able%20to%20highlight%20these%20challenges%20in%20front%20of%20IAS%20trainees%20at%20LBSNAA.%20He%20also%20advised%20them%20to%20not%20rely%20on%20junior%20officers%20only%2C%20and%20to%20visit%20farmers%E2%80%99%20sites%20on%20their%20own%20to%20understand%20the%20challenges%20at%20the%20grassroots%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFarmers%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20progress%20with%20farming%20alone.%20After%20sowing%2C%20it%20takes%20five%20months%20to%20generate%20income%20from%20the%20crop.%20Du